The paper deals with automated verification of modal logic, which is a subfield of mathematical logic. The use of automated reasoning tools and the focus on embedding modal logic in classical higher-order logic suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. However, the paper also deals with automated theorem proving and verification, which are topics that fall under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of modal logic in knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a topic in Logic and Computation (cs.LG) and Programming Languages (cs.PL).
